Andhra Pradesh Motor Sports Club (APMSC) is an automobile racing association in the state of Andhra Pradesh, India which was established in 1977. The Club has participated in Gymkhana and TSD Rallies up until 1982, when the “Charminar Challenge” concept was established.
The club has been organising rallies which took the team to Maharashtra, Karnataka and Andhra Pradesh. The club participated all over India. Notable teams included Kiran Mody and team and the Pestonjee Viccajee team.
The club started conducting events in frequent intervals from 2008 onwards, and tied up with new partners and sponsors. Drag racing was introduced in Andhra Pradesh by events named as "Deccan Quarter Mile Drag [DQMD]".
